'''Turamarth''' is [[Sindarin]] for "Master of Doom", a title [[Túrin]] gave himself while living in the forest of [[Brethil]] in the [[First Age]].<ref>{{S|Appendix}}, ''amarth''</ref>

==Etymology==
''[[tur]]'' "master, lord" and ''[[amarth]]'' "doom"

==Cognates==
*[[Quenya]] ''Turambar''
